
Source: https://blog.pentesteracademy.com/from-zip-slip-to-system-takeover-8564433ea542

It can result in:

    Path Traversal
    Symlink file overwrite
    
Path Traversal

If a vulnerable code extracts a user-supplied zip archive, that can lead to arbitrary file overwrite, where an attacker can overwrite arbitrary files on the system, based on the privileges the application is running with.

If the application code runs as root, itâ€™s game over: The attacker can overwrite critical files like passwd, shadow, .bashrc, .htpasswd, authorized_keys, etc.


Ex: 

touch __init__.py
sudo mkdir -p /app/application
sudo cp __init__.py /app/application
tar -czvf init.tag.gz --absolute-names '../../../../../../../../../../../../../../app/application/__init__.py'
